Born to Make You Happy is a teen pop song that lasts for four minutes and three seconds.cite web url=http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0028935 title=Britney Spears Born to Make You Happy  Digital Sheet Music work=Music Notes publisher=Universal Music Publishing Group accessdate=December 23, 2010citeweb url=http://new.music.yahoo.com/britney-spears/tracks/born-to-make-you-happy--1486506 title=Born to Make You Happy by Britney Spears publisher=Yahoo! Music accessdate=March 6, 2011 The song is composed in the Key music key of D major and is set in time signature of common time, with a moderately slow tempo of 88 beats per minute. Spears vocal range spans over an octave, from Fmusic sharp3 to B4. The song's lyrics talks about a relationship that a woman desires to correct, not quite understanding what went wrong, as she comes to realize that I don't know how to live without your love/I was born to make you happy.citeweb url=http://newsroom.mtv.com/2010/03/03/britney-spears-baby-one-more-time/ title=Britney Spears Goes Back To Her Schoolgirl Days For The First Installment Of 'Popology' date=March 3, 2010 last=Anderson first=Kyle work=MTV publisher=MTV Networks accessdate=March 5, 2011 The song has a basic sequence of BmGDA as its chord progression.

Reception
Critical response
Born to Make You Happy received mixed reviews from music critics. Kyle Anderson of MTV considered the song's chorus more than a little bit off-putting, saying the first lines of it could be a sentiment that a lovelorn 16-year-old can understand, but it also sounds like Spears is in training to be a geisha. Craig MacInnis of Hamilton Spectator said Born to Make You Happy verge on the sort of boy-worshipping dreck that even Tiffany singer Tiffany would have sniffedat.citeweb url=http://travel.canoe.ca/AllPop-SpearsBritney/cd_baby1.html last=MacInnis first=Craig title=Bopper babe's CD glib collection of cliches date=January 12, 1999  publisher=Hamilton Spectator. Metroland Media Group accessdate=March 5, 2011 Mike Ross of Edmond Sun said, as Spears emotes in the song, the message behind the music is worse than mere sweet nothings. ... So much for Girl Power.citeweb url=http://travel.canoe.ca/AllPop-SpearsBritney/cd_baby3.html last=Ross first=Mike title=Britney Spears fails miserably date=January 23, 1999  publisher=Edmond Sun. Community Newspaper Holdings accessdate=March 5, 2011 Amanda Murray of Sputnikmusic considered Born to Make You Happy a proficient but entirely unrememberable song,citeweb url=http://www.sputnikmusic.com/review/5825/Britney-Spears-...Baby-One-More-Time/ title=Britney Spears - ...Baby One More Time Staff Review last=Murray first=Amanda publisher=Sputnikmusic date=March 26, 2006 accessdate=March 5, 2011 while Andy Petch-Jex of musicOMH considered the song an early classic.citeweb url=http://www.musicomh.com/albums/britney-spears.htm last=Petch-Jex first=Andy title=Britney Spears - Greatest Hits: My Prerogative - Album Review date=November 8, 2004 publisher=musicOMH accessdate=March 5, 2011

Chart performance
Born to Make You Happy achieved commercial success, reaching the top-five in eleven countries. On the week of January 20, 2000, the song debuted atop the charts in Irish Singles Chart Ireland,citeweb url=http://www.chart-track.co.uk/index.jsp?c=p%2Fmusicvideo%2Fmusic%2Farchive%2Findex_test.jsp&ct=240001&arch=t&lyr=2000&year=2000&week=3 title=GFK Chart Track - Britney Spears - Born to Make You Happy publisher=Irish Singles Chart date=January 20, 2000 accessdate=March 5, 2011 while debuting at the same position in the The Official Charts Company United Kingdom on the week of January 29, 2000.citeweb url=http://www.chartstats.com/songinfo.php?id=27929 title=Chart Stats - Britney Spears - Born to Make You Happy publisher=The Official Charts Company date=January 29, 2000 accessdate=March 5, 2011 The song was certified Silver by the British Phonographic Industry BPI in the country, for selling over 200,000 units of the single.cite web   publisher=British Phonographic Industry   title=BPI Certified Awards Searchable Database   date=January 28, 2000   url=http://www.bpi.co.uk/certifiedawards/search.aspx   accessdate=August 8, 2010   deadurl=no Born to Make You Happy reached number two on the European Hot 100 Singles European chart,cite web   author=Sexton, Paul   title=Gabrielle, R.E.M. Debut High On U.K. Singles Chart    publisher=Billboard magazine Billboard. Prometheus Global Media   date=January 31, 2000   url=http://www.billboard.com/bbcom/search/google/article_display.jsp?vnu_content_id=869289#/bbcom/search/google/article_display.jsp?vnu_content_id=869289   accessdate=August 8, 2010 and peaked at number four in Sverigetopplistan Sweden on the week of December 23, 1999, reaching number two in the following. The song was certified Platinum by the International Federation of the Phonographic Industry IFPI in the country, for selling over 40,000 units of the single.cite web   publisher=International Federation of the Phonographic Industry   work=IFPI Sweden   title=Certifications   date=2000   url=http://www.ifpi.se/wp/wp-content/uploads/ar-20021.pdf   accessdate=August 8, 2010   deadurl=no In Media Control Charts Germany, the song was certified Gold,cite gold platin  accessdate=August 8, 2010 and reached number three on the charts. The lowest chart position for Born to Make You Happy was in SNEP France, where it reached number nine,citeweb url=http://www.lescharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Britney+Spears&titel=Born+to+Make+You+Happy&cat=s title=Lescharts.com  Britney Spears  Born to Make You Happy publisher=Les Charts & Hung Medien / lescharts.com accessdate=March 5, 2011 and was certified Silver by the Syndicat National de l'dition Phonographique SNEP.cite web   publisher=Syndicat National de l'dition Phonographique   work=Disque en France   title=Certifications Singles Argent   date=May 10, 2000   url=http://www.disqueenfrance.com/fr/pag-259165-CERTIFICATIONS.html?year=2000   accessdate=August 8, 2010   deadurl=no

Promotion
Music video
Image:Bsbtoyh.jpg right thumb The music video for Born to Make You Happy features Spears in a futuristic room.
The music video for Born to Make You Happy was directed by Billie Woodruff and produced by Geneva Films,cite video  people=Spears, Britney  date=November 9, 2004  title=Greatest Hits: My Prerogative  url=http://www.amazon.com/Britney-Spears-Greatest-Hits-Prerogative/dp/B00064AM62/ref=sr_1_2?s=music&ie=UTF8&qid=1296789429&sr=1-2  format=DVD  medium=  language=English  publisher=Zomba/Jive Label Group  location=  archiveurl=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0480109/  archivedate=2004  accessdate=February 4, 2011  time=  id=  isbn=B00064AM62  oclc=  quote=  ref=  while choreographed by Wade Robson.citeweb url=http://www.msaagency.com/pr/msa/wade-robson.aspx title=Wade Robson, Producer/Director/Choreographer publisher=McDonald / Selznick Associates accessdate=March 7, 2011 It begins with a shot of Spears sleeping in her room, as the scene fades and start to picture her dream. At the beggining of her dream, Spears is wearing a shiny silver outfit, and sitting in a blue and silver futuristic room with several different levels, where she sings and walk around. Following this part of the video, Spears appears atop the apartment building she lives, performing a dance segment in a red top and black skirt with a few backup dancers. After the first dance segment, Spears is seen wearing white clothes and singing at the room she is sleeping. Before the end of video, Spears dream that her love interest come into her room to see her, while the pair start a pillow fight, which she wins. The closing shot shows Spears still slepping, but now with a smile upon her face. A longer dance segment intercalates with all the scenes during the whole video.

Live performances
Born to Make You Happy was performed by Spears on four tours. On her first tour, ...Baby One More Time Tour, she sang the song seated on a starcaise,cite news url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/e/a/1999/07/30/WEEKEND10994.dtl&type=printable title=The musical equivalent of cotton candy date=July 30, 1999 accessdate=January 1, 2010 last=Ganahl first=Jane publisher=San Francisco Chronicle. Hearst Corporation while on her second tour, ...Baby One More Time Tour Crazy 2k Tour, the performance of the song included a full dance segment.cite news url=http://www.cm-life.com/2000/03/17/oopsbritneydrivesuscrazyonemoretime/ title=Oops! Britney Drives Us Crazy One More Time date=March 17, 2000 accessdate=January 16, 2010 last=Graham first=Adam  publisher=Central Michigan Life. Central Michigan University On 2000s Oops!... I Did It Again World Tour, Spears perfomed Born to Make You Happy wearing pajamas and slippers, with a dance segment near the end.cite news url=http://www.pitch.com/2000-07-20/music/britney-spears-mikaila&page=211 title=Britney Spears/Mikaila date=July 20, 2000 accessdate=January 20, 2010 last=Miller first=Andrew  publisher=The Pitch newspaper The Pitch. Village Voice Media Born to Make You Happy was performed for the last time on Dream Within a Dream Tour, where Spears emerged from the middle of a giant musical box on the stage as a ballerina, to perform the song in a medley with Lucky Britney Spears song Lucky and Sometimes Britney Spears song Sometimes, right after the performance of Overprotected.cite news url=http://livedesignonline.com/mag/britneys_big_splash/index.html?smte=wr title=Britney's Big Splash date=July 1, 2002 accessdate=February 4, 2010 last=McHugh first=Catherine  publisher=Live Design. Penton Mediacite news url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1450487/20011102/spears_britney.jhtml title=Britney Goes Bald, Plays Tiny Dancer, Gets Caught In The Rain At Tour Kickoff last=Reid first=Shaheem last2=Moss first2=Corey date=November 2, 2001 work=MTV publisher=MTV Networks accessdate=January 6, 2010

